# JavaScript / TypeScript testing conventions

The canonical rule content lives in [`coding-rules/rules/testing-js.md`](mdc:coding-rules/rules/testing-js.md) — shared with Claude Code so the tools cannot drift.

When writing or editing JS/TS tests, read and follow `coding-rules/rules/testing-js.md`: co-located test files, behavior-driven test names, Testing Library query priority, network-layer mocking, state isolation, the snapshot policy, and the flaky-test playbook.
